==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Raumur
<hw>R⟦eacute⟧`au`mur"</hw> <pr>(r⟦asl⟧`⟦omac⟧`m⟦usdot⟧r")</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to <person>Ren⟦eacute⟧ Antoine
Ferchault de <etsep>R⟦eacute⟧aumur</etsep></person>; conformed to the
scale adopted by <person>R⟦eacute⟧aumur</person> in graduating the
thermometer he invented.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A
R⟦eacute⟧aumur thermometer or scale.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <xex>R⟦eacute⟧aumur thermometer</xex> is so
graduated that 0⟦deg⟧ marks the freezing point and 80⟦deg⟧ the boiling
point of water. Frequently indicated by R. Cf. <er>Centigrade</er>, and
<er>Fahrenheit</er>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Thermometer</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reave</ent>⟦br⟧
